Pour the @water{300%ml} for the rice into a #medium saucepan{} with a
#tight-fitting lid{}. Stir in the @basmati rice{150%g}, @salt{1/4%tsp} and
bring to the boil. Once boiling, turn the heat down to medium and cover with
the lid.

Leave to cook for ~{10%minutes}, then remove the #pan from the heat (still
covered) and leave to the side for another ~{10%minutes} or until ready to
serve (the rice will continue to cook in its own steam).

Meanwhile, heat a drizzle of @oil{drizzle} in a #large frying pan{} on
medium-high heat. Once hot, add the @diced chicken breast{260%g} and season
with @salt{} and @pepper{}. Fry until browned all over, ~{5-6%minutes}. Turn
occasionally.

> IMPORTANT: Wash your hands and equipment after handling raw chicken and its
> packaging.

While the chicken cooks, halve the @green pepper{1} and discard the core and
seeds. Chop into 2cm chunks. Peel and grate the @garlic clove{1} (or use a
#garlic press{}).

Once browned, add the pepper to the chicken and cook until starting to soften,
~{3-4%minutes}. Stir in the garlic and @rogan josh curry paste{50%g} and cook
for ~{1%minute} more, then stir in the @tomato passata{1} and
@chicken stock paste{10%g} and @water{100%ml} for the curry.

Bring the curry to a boil, then lower the heat and simmer until the chicken is
cooked through and the sauce has thickened, ~{10-15%minutes}.

> IMPORTANT: The chicken is cooked when no longer pink in the middle.

Once cooked, taste the curry and season with @salt{} and @pepper{}. Add some
@?chilli flakes{1%pinch} if you'd like some more heat (careful, they're hot),
then stir through the @mango chutney{40%g}.

Fluff up the rice with a #fork{}, then share between your #bowls{}.

Top with the chicken rogan josh and sprinkle with the
@toasted flaked almonds{15%g} to finish. Enjoy!